Package: blblm
Type: Package
Title: Linear Modeling with Little Bag of Bootstraps
Version: 1.0.0
Author: Jessica LaCourse, Randy Lai
Maintainer: The package maintainer <jllacourse@ucdavis.edu>
Description: The bag of little bootstraps (BLB) is a procedure 
    that takes the best of subsampling and bootstrapping to yield 
    a robust and efficient analytical tool. 
    BLB's primary use is for assessing the quality of estimators.
